    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1771"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1771">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/95.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering telegram of May 20. I suggest cases of Harrington, Ross, Morris and
                    Lathrope and possibly Rahlin.<note n="11" xml:id="d1771fn11">Miscellaneous cases
                        occurring after 1912.</note> These are all the cases pending prior to last
                    two riots except the cases of soldiers and civilians connected with Fourth of
                    July 1912 Cocoa Grove riot.</p>
                <p>My suggestion however related rather to attempting to settle all cases by direct
                    demand and negotiation including the possibility of obtaining a lump sum
                    covering all, than to submitting all of them together to arbitration unless we
                    could obtain from Panama admission of liability as to all of them in same terms
                    as in the Fourth of July cases.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
